<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Selenite</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, I'm posting this here (though I've already sent in suggestions to Verant) to try and gain some support for what I think might be one of the few ideas that has a hope of successfully getting this spawn altered.  I'll start by examining the situation.<P>1. Verant wants a bottleneck for Ragefire.<BR>2. They wanted to make it even slower - they succeeded when they did us the 'favor' of moving him to Skyfire.<BR>3. They aren't going to remove the bottleneck.<BR>4. They probably won't even switch it back to the way it was.<P>There is however, a switch they can make that will, while not removing the bottleneck, help a little, in my opinion.  That is, reverse the spawn timers on the two Ragefires.<P>Have the pearl hand-in Ragefire be the bottleneck, and the dragon Ragefire be a once-a-day spawn.  Why?  This'll allow people to worry far less about being KS'd.  Let's face it, one of the reasons many of us have trouble with this spawn is because guilds that are bigger, stronger, and more used to racing can just roll right over those of us who can defeat him, but need a little more time to gather forces.<P>It also won't remove the bottleneck, something which I'm relatively sure Verant will not do.  What it will do is bring all contention down to one thing - who can click trade fastest.  I mean, it may not be a great test of skill, I guess....but at least in my opinion, it would be less inconveniencing to a large number of people - namely, all those non-clerics that are currently forced to sit there camping the Skyfire spawn with you, just so you don't get KS'd.<P>I know that I, for one, would feel a LOT better if I could do the bottleneck portion myself, alone, with no need to waste the time of a large number of friends.<P>If anyone thinks this idea has any merit, please communicate it to Verant as best you can - comments on their boards, feedback in game, e-mails, whatever.  All of them or one of them, whatever ye have time for.  Maybe this will help us out, a little.  It won't make our quest as easy as, say, Monks or Druids have it, which it would be, if Ragefire was a relatively fast-spawning, triggerable mob, but it will hopefully resolve at least a portion of our problems.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Daynan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This is actually a kind of good idea. It allows people to kill the dragon at ease without all the rushing and stress. won't be done though because too many people have probably already turned in their pearls.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Crysina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I too like this idea.<P>Crys</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Viscera</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">According to several Fan Faire reports (check Graffe's), the Ragefire spawn <B>is</B> bugged, since he is not spawning "every several days" like Verant intended. They are working on it, and they have said it is related to the same bug that is not spawning Vulak.<P>So, expect a fix in the near future, making the Ragefire spawntime a more manageable 2-3 days.<P>------------------<BR>Viscera Galen<BR>L60 High Priest of Brell<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">varthdadur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I posted this very idea way back when they first changed the quest.  It got lost in all the posts but I still think its a great idea.<P>My point at that time was if you really wanted ragefire without being KS'd then you had to have a raid of 20 people standing around waiting.  That's a lot of wasted time.  Talk about waiting 50 hours for your spawn...well multiply that by 20 people and you got a lot of real time wasted.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Baron Varth L60 High Priest<BR>Mogwa L51 Monk</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
